News Website (HTML & CSS)

A responsive and visually structured News Website built using HTML and CSS.
This project focuses on creating a clean news layout that displays different categories of news such as technology, sports, politics, and entertainment in an organized and user-friendly way.

The goal of this project was to practice frontend web development, improve UI layout skills, and understand how real-world news portals structure their content.

Project Overview

This website simulates a basic online news portal where users can easily browse news articles. The homepage displays multiple news sections with headlines, images, and short descriptions to make reading easier and engaging.

The design focuses on clarity, readability, and structured content presentation, similar to popular news platforms.

Features
1. Structured News Layout

The website organizes news articles into different sections such as:

Latest News

Technology

Sports

Entertainment

Trending Stories

2. Responsive Design

The layout is designed to adjust across different screen sizes to provide a better user experience.

3. Clean UI Design

The website uses a simple and clean interface so that users can easily focus on reading news content.

4. Navigation Bar

A navigation menu allows users to quickly access different news categories.

5. News Cards

Each news article is displayed in a card-style layout with:

Headline

Image

Short description

Read more section

Technologies Used

HTML5 – Used to structure the content of the website

CSS3 – Used for styling, layout, and responsiveness

No external frameworks were used in order to strengthen core frontend skills.

